---
description: Keep native pull-to-refresh spinner hidden in mobile
alwaysApply: true
---

# Mobile Pull To Refresh Without Native Spinner

- In the mobile app, do not expose the platform `RefreshControl` spinner to the user.
- Use `PickleRefreshScrollView` or `PageLayout` with `pullToRefresh` instead of adding ad-hoc `RefreshControl` UI.
- Preserve the custom `PickleballRefreshIndicator` as the only visible refresh indicator.
- If `RefreshControl` is required internally, keep its spinner fully transparent using the existing `PickleRefreshScrollView` pattern.
- Do not add visible mask panels, white overlays, or extra placeholder blocks in the refresh zone.
- Do not replace the custom pull-to-refresh experience with the default iOS or Android spinner.

## Examples

```tsx
// Good
<PageLayout
  pullToRefresh={{ refreshing, onRefresh }}
>
  {children}
</PageLayout>

// Good
<PickleRefreshScrollView refreshing={refreshing} onRefresh={onRefresh}>
  {children}
</PickleRefreshScrollView>

// Bad
<ScrollView
  refreshControl={<RefreshControl refreshing={refreshing} onRefresh={onRefresh} />}
/>
```
